criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Being evaluated in the emergency department for suicidal ideation/suicide attempt;

          2. Deemed medically stable by ED physician;

          3. Age greater than or equal to 18 years old;

          4. Able and willing to have telephone follow up at 1 week;

          5. Report at least one firearm in the home

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Unable to participate medically or cognitively (e.g. sustained altered level of
             consciousness, hostility, psychosis, sexual assault victim, severe vomiting or pain);

          2. Currently in legal custody;

          3. Live in group home or other supervised custody;

          4. Already enrolled
